This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms in sensitive contexts, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the issue of fairness in algorithmic decision making, which is a topic that is relevant to the sub-categories of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
